    {
      "id": "f7e2a656d6bd8d6ca4091f0693f158691cab6d7d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-07 16:24:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: (3 inline comments)\n\nIn addition to my comments, I think there is another potentially unexpected failure case:\n\nprocess1:\nopen file\ntry write, generate error (recorded in async_rc);\n(not closing yet)\nprocess2:\nopen file\ntry write, succeed.\nclose (will get error from async rc because of process1)\n\nto avoid most unexpected pasrt of it, I guess we can also check async_rc in open and set \"saw error\" in struct file if async_rc is set.\nThough I guess we don't have a clear way to distribute errors properly between two processes if both of them are writing into the same file on the same node and some writes fail only for one of those processes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "85128e13c0a01088c795a2331bd1ba3c3b82a9af",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-08-08 05:14:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: (3 inline comments)\n\n> In addition to my comments, I think there is another potentially unexpected failure case:\n> process1: open file try write, generate error (recorded in async_rc); (not closing yet) process2: open file try write, succeed. close (will get error from async rc because of process1)\n\nFor most cases, write() called succeed does not means the data are really written back to storage. When close() error, we cannot distinguish whether it is process1's async failure or the process2's.\n\nThere is no way to totally distinguish which process is the owner of the async error. This patch is just try to avoid redundant error message when close().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "d616f4d3605c95fb21948a896676d8a1d60d9827",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
